;Pledge for a Healthy Internet
Aseḥbiber ɣef Internet zeddigen


;The open, global internet is the most powerful communication and collaboration resource we have ever seen. It embodies some of our deepest hopes for human progress. It enables new opportunities for learning, building a sense of shared humanity, and solving the pressing problems facing people everywhere.
Internet yeldin, amaḍlan d taɣbalut n teqwalt akked umɛiwen tameqqrant ugar, uǧin tettwassen ar ass-a. Yegber kra n yisaramen-nneɣ igejdanen i usfari n umdan. Yettmuddu tignatin timaynutin n ulmad, d tneflit n uḥulfu n uttekki tucrikt ar talsa akked ferru n wuguren uzriben i d-ttmagaren yemdanen deg umaḍal.


;Over the last decade we have seen this promise fulfilled in many ways. We have also seen the power of the internet used to magnify divisiveness, incite violence, promote hatred, and intentionally manipulate fact and reality. We have learned that we should more explicitly set out our aspirations for the human experience of the internet. We do so now.
Di mraw n yiseggasen ineggura, nwala amiru-agi iḍerru-d  s waṭas n yiberdan. Nwala daɣen amek yezmer ad yettwaseqdec Internet akken ad yeglu s beṭṭu gar yimdanen, asiwem ar tekriḍt, asnerni n kaṛuh d ubeddel n tilawt. Nwala d akken yessefk ad nɛiwed tamuɣli deg wayen nessaram deg useqdec n Internet. Ad t-nxeddem akka tura.


;We are committed to an internet that includes all the peoples of the earth — where a person’s demographic characteristics do not determine their online access, opportunities, or quality of experience.
Nesseḥbibir ɣef Internet ara d-yegren akk iɣerfan n umadal : tawennaḍt anida ayen yessemgaraden imdanen ur yessefk ara ad isemgarad aseqdec n internet, ar tezmert yettunefken neɣ ar tɣara n termit srid.


;We are committed to an internet that promotes civil discourse, human dignity, and individual expression.
Negzem-itt di ṛṛay akken ad nseḥbiber ɣef internet yettmuddun tagnit i ummeslay aɣarim, isseɣ n umdan akken tilelli n ummeslay i yal yiwen.


;We are committed to an internet that elevates critical thinking, reasoned argument, shared knowledge, and verifiable facts.
Nettmuddu afud i internet yessalayen azal n tiktiwin n usenqden, awal s ttbut, beṭṭu n tmussniwin akked usenqed n wayen iḍerrun.


;We are committed to an internet that catalyzes collaboration among diverse communities working together for the common good.
Nessiḥbibir ɣef internet yettmuddun afud i umwiwen gar tirebbaɛ akken ad izmirent ad xedment lwaḥid ɣef wayen yelhan.


;Show Your Support
Sken-d afud-ik


;An internet with these qualities will not come to life on its own. Individuals and organizations must embed these aspirations into internet technology and into the human experience with the internet. The Mozilla Manifesto and Addendum represent Mozilla’s commitment to advancing these aspirations. We aim to work together with people and organizations everywhere who share these goals to make the internet an even better place for everyone.
Internet s tɣara-agi ur yezmir ara ad d-ilal i yiman-is. Imdanen akked tuddsiwin yessefk ad ddun ar isaramen-agi di tlemmast n titiknulujiyin n internet akked wassaɣen yellan gar yimdanen d internet. Ameskan n Mozilla d wayen i d-yernan, mmalen-d asiḥbiber n Mozilla i usnerni n yisaramen-agi. Iswi-nneɣ d axeddim akked yimdanen d tuddsiwin yebḍan yid-neɣ iswiyen-agiakken ad nerr internet d amḍiq icebḥen ugar i yal yiwen.


